# EigenSkills Project Standards

## First Steps for New Conversations

Before exploring the codebase, read `AGENTS.md` at the project root.
It contains the complete file map, API contracts, and implementation status.

## Architecture

Three components:
1. **Skill Registry** — curated GitHub repo at https://github.com/38d3b7/eigenskills, indexed by registry.json, GitHub Action validates
2. **Agent Container** — Docker image deployed per-user to EigenCompute TEE (viem wallet, EigenAI routing, sandboxed skill execution)
3. **Platform** — Next.js frontend + Express backend, SIWE auth, orchestrates EigenCompute deploys

## Key Conventions

- Agent wallet derivation uses **viem** (`mnemonicToAccount`), not ethers
- EigenAI model: `gpt-oss-120b-f16` (only documented model)
- EigenAI Sepolia: `https://eigenai-sepolia.eigencloud.xyz/v1/chat/completions`
- EigenAI Mainnet: `https://eigenai.eigencloud.xyz/v1/chat/completions`
- Dockerfile must use `--platform=linux/amd64` and `USER root`
- Env vars ending in `_PUBLIC` are visible on-chain; all others are encrypted in TEE
- Skills declare `requires_env` — executor only passes those vars to subprocess
- Auth is SIWE (Sign In With Ethereum), no passwords
- No staking contract — curated registry is the trust model
- **EigenCompute deploys use `@layr-labs/ecloud-sdk`** (TypeScript SDK, no Docker/CLI needed). See `backend/src/eigencompute-sdk.ts`. The `DEPLOY_STRATEGY` env var controls the path: `sdk` (default), `github-actions`, or `cli`.

